t in the outflowing gas, dense outflowing clouds have\nshorter lifetime and that they evaporate into the diffuse component along the\noutflow or, more simply, that diffuse clouds are more efficiently accelerated\nto larger distances by radiation pressure.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Apr 2012 10:45:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Jun 2012 17:26:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
